<br>
I think that is is dishonest to claim that anyone in the world does not know what STOP means. I know Americans are trained to hold up a hand too. Americans usually yell HALT as well, so please don't make the bad arguement that you need to speak english to understand STOP. If a French policeman yelled HALT at an American we would stop, and you know how few Americans speak a second language. <br>
<br>
Americans are the same as the brits in this regard, it just gets milage when you can say American's shot innocents. If you are too stupid to understand stop, what are we supposed to do? We have people using car bombs, and they dont mark BOMB is any language at all on the side of the car. Troops have to assume they are car bombs if they don't stop.<br>
